      "date": "2012-08-15 05:37:26.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 9: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(1 inline comment)\n\nPatch needs a fixup to avoid spurious warning massages that would not apply in case nsec timestamps are not working on some systems yet.\n\nWhen it is rebased, it should be done against master, since this could be landed before the actual nsec timestamps support is landed.  That would ensure the testing works when nsec support is not available (e.g. against old servers), and conversely allows older tools to start using nsec timestamps as soon as they are available.",
